17/01/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Serbian Foreign Minister Vuk Jeremic, his Turkish counterpart Ahmet Davutoglu and Bosnia and Herzegovina's (BiH) top diplomat Sven Alkalaj held talks Friday (January 15th) in Belgrade.
They reiterated that good relations in the Western Balkans are the most important prerequisite for the region's prosperity and its EU integration.
Davutoglu and Jeremic both said their governments strongly support BiH's territorial integrity and sovereignty, while Alkalaj pledged to boost ties.
A similar meeting took place in Zagreb on Thursday, with Alkalaj and Davutoglu conferring with Croatian Foreign Minister Gordan Jandrokovic.
(B92, Tanjug, Danas - 15/01/10)
